      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        To be included, the teeth to be restored had to:

          1. be asymptomatic

          2. have occlusal and adjacent teeth in contact

          3. have cavity sizes exceeding the one-third of the bucco-lingual distance between cusp
             tips -

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with periodontitis, poor oral hygiene, bruxism or a history of allergic
             reactions to any of the materials
